race.comment: BAS RELIEF (11) is a filly by Brazen Beau on debut for the McEvoy yard who has looked the goods winning a recent Flemington jumpout. She's found a nice race to kick off in and should go very well. ESMAHLI (6) is a colt by Blue Point on debut for the Hayes yard who has trialled well leading in. Represents strong connections here and should be running a bold race. BOYD (3) has race experience on his side, debuting in a hot maiden at Ballarat before two sound efforts since. He's speedy, rolls forward from the wide gate and might well have the race craft to put the newcomers away. DONATO (5) was poor last time at Kilmore but had been good on debut and is a possible improver. GOOD ONYA CHAMP (7) resumes off a trial win and might be ready to show more this time in.
